         <div type="translation" xml:lang="eng" resp="part:emfr">
         	<p>Prosperity! Fortune!</p>
         	<p>Twenty-sixth year of the victorious king Nṛpatuṅgavikramavarman.</p>
         	<p>Hand-written <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>kai-y-eḻuttu</foreign></supplied> document <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>āvaṇam<!--or Āvaṇam? cf. TG--></foreign></supplied> for the price of a land <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>nila-vilai</foreign>, that is, sale-deed</supplied> <supplied reason="subaudible">by</supplied> We, the members of the assembly <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign><hi rend="grantha">sabhai</hi>yōm</foreign></supplied> of Uttaramērucaturvedimaṅgalam in the Kāliyūr-k-kōṭṭam <!--Update to "district of K"?--> and the division of the same <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>taṉ kūṟṟu</foreign>, that is, literally, "in the division of itself"</supplied>.
         	</p>
         	<p>
         		<supplied reason="subaudible">In</supplied> Kūkūr, in the Viḷā-nāṭu, in the western division <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>mī-kūṟṟu</foreign></supplied>, in the Muttaraiyar-nāṭu, to Pūti Tīraṉ alias Vicaiyanalluḷāṉ Kāṭavati <supplied reason="subaudible">of</supplied> Kūkūr, the whole of Kīl-p-pūṇṭi <supplied reason="explanation">literally, "the eastern village/hamlet"</supplied>, which lies fallow <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>kiṭanta</foreign></supplied> without being ...<!--Update!--> <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>kūṟiṭātē</foreign></supplied>, in the southern hamlet <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>paṭākai</foreign></supplied> of our village, east of the Peruṅ-kōṭu lake <!--update: add literal translation-->, south of Āṭalam Pūṇṭi<!--add gap-->
         	</p>
         </div>
      	
